All 5 case-isolates belonged to sequence type 171 and were blaKPC-3-positive. Three pulsed-field gel electrophoresis patterns with >90% similarity were identified in the 5 case-isolates. We identified overlaps in time and location between case patients. Plasmid types and resistance genes were nearly identical between the isolates. Whole genome sequencing showed isolates A, B, and D to be closely related with <10 core single-nucleotide polymorphisms differences. Isolates C and E were also closely related to each other, but more distantly to A, B, and D; all belonged to the clonal lineage of the major circulating E. cloacae complex strain in Minnesota and North Dakota. Despite having overlapping hospital stays, isolates for patients C and D were not identical.
