Results
This study included 154 patients (115 IDC and 39 non-IDC). Guideline adherence was significantly greater in the IDC group 78% versus 46% in the non-IDC group (P < .001). Significantly more patients in the IDC group had echocardiography (91% vs 67%; P < .001) and follow-up blood cultures (92% vs 64%; P > .001). Mortality was also greater in the non-IDC group (23%) versus 5% for the IDC group (P = .001).
Conclusions
Patients with SAB receiving an IDC were more likely to receive guideline-congruent management and had significantly reduced mortality. No improvements in antibiotic choice or dosing were observed, likely a result of ASP review."
}
@article{KALP2017589,
