Results
A total of 117 patients received vaginal operative preparation during the course of the study, with 64 patients in group 1 and 53 patients in group 2. Of the patients in group 1, 60 (93.7%) reported no vaginal irritation, 3 (4.69%) reported mild irritation, and 1 (1.56%) reported moderate irritation. In group 2 (2% CHG vaginal preparation), all of the patients (100%) reported no vaginal irritation (P = .38).
