Methods
PubMed and EMBASE were searched by 2 researchers. High and normal BMIs were defined as ≥25 and 18.5-24.99, respectively. Odds ratios (ORs) were calculated to compare the pooled effect sizes. The primary outcome was mortality. The secondary outcome was infectious outcomes, including surgical site, pulmonary infections, and urinary tract infections.
